reviews_data.review_text: Casual but classy place with the best priced wine and crafted beer selections in the South Park area. I love the outdoor patio when the weather is warm.  Also, great sandwiches and delicious soups every day! The GM is Bora. He is so kind, and he gives excellent service. Highly recommend!. They have a new selection of beers at different times.
This is a great place.

reviews_data.review_text: Waited over an hour for a chicken salad sandwich that was full of bones.
A great place for remote workers or a lunch date.

Listen my partner comes in consistently to get us breakfast and for the last week 03-17 through 03-23  around 9-11am the breakfast feel
Skimpy like there no love in those sandwiches

I’m not sure if they changed the crew or what’s happening but they’re usually amazing made with flavor and properly portioned lately we only get egg on one half of the sandwich, it’s an insane down grade of what we always get.
Very good food and great atmosphere
The Stack High was a Low Blow. Was not stacked with meat and it was tough to chew. Not ordering that again. 😕 I did like the chips though.
Great price for a sandwich or salad thats quick. But great quality!

this place looks awesome, everyone inside is amazing and the food is perfect! (we got breakfast) the bagels and contents were delicious and cooked to perfection. plenty of vegetarian and vegan options. coffee was 10/10 too. barista there actually cares! the outdoor area is huge and well spaced out yet very comfortable.

Good service, food is delicious. Trendy place, great location, SouthPark, high quality everything. Coffee is great, even in the afternoon.
Nice staff brought over my coffee.

Rhino Market & Deli in SouthPark, Charlotte, is a versatile neighborhood spot offering a delightful dining experience. The best part about Rhino is their grille, which features made-to-order sandwiches, such as the Chicken Torta and Portobello Sandwich, as well as amazing breakfast burritos. The extensive selection of craft beers and wines complements the menu, and the double patios provide a pleasant atmosphere for relaxation. With friendly service and a convenient location, it's an excellent choice for a casual meal or gathering with friends or colleagues.

Good basic tasty breakfast items including large portion French toast. Select brewed gourmet coffees and lattes available. Wine, beer and other branded items sold on site. Bar on one side and outdoor seating available.
Best deli in charlotte. Amazing vegetarian selection.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Healthy Hummus, Fresco Veggie Sandwich, Breakfast Burrito, Designer Egg Salad Sandwich, Grilled Cheese

reviews_data.review_text: Friendly staff and good coffee
the staff is very nice
Uptown and Southend locations are awesome. SouthPark locations service and  kitchen staff is insanely slow. 3 Sundays in a row, the wait for a single bfast burrito has been 30+ minutes.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dan
Very sorry about this and thank you for the feedback. Seems like we are short staffed on Sundays or something else is going on.

Can we offer you a gift card for the inconvenience?

reviews_data.review_text:
One of my favorite locations. Super quick and nice walkable area after grabbing a bite to eat.

Love the new coffee options, just what I needed!

Chicken torta is a fan favorite of mine 😁
Food is always consistently good. It gets busy around lunch time during the week but mostly pretty chill
Always good when I go

Great patio, friendly staff, and good drink selection.

Was on the happy bus and came in for a bottle of wine. The guy at the register commented about how he was not a fan. Cool not for everyone but when I came back to the register with a 17.99 Prosecco  and got back on the bus then the next day looked at my account and was charged $38.. very sketchy so check your receipt here

Note

reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, you left a similar review for the W. Morehead location. Can you please contact us, and let us know the date and location that this occurred so we can look into your transaction?

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve always heard great things about Rhino so I stopped by this Saturday morning for a quick bite.   I love that they have a whole section dedicated to veggie sandwiches! The Chaud Legumes was a 10/10 & Healthy Hummus was a pretty good as well. The Caesar salad had pecans in it which added a nice twist. I will be back :)
Consistently delicious
Always great food, coffee, snacks, sweet treats and positive vibes. Great for remote work, a meeting or just hanging with friends and family. I love the ability to order online now!!!
Went w my daughter, very good sandwich. Leas than fast food tooo
Awesomeness

Absolutely love rhino market but the past couple times I’ve got a to-go order have rubbed me wrong. The Sicilian is my personal favorite but this is what my sandwich has looked like my past couple of orders…What am I paying for? PLEASE DO BETTER

Very cool place that I just figured out existed. If you're trying to lay off the booze or take a break they have CBD liquor and drinks they're about the same price as alcohol and relax you. It's a great spot to just chill and find different things from a full-service bar, live music, full service food, and CBD products if you're trying to take a break

Love, Love, Love Rhino Market. I used to go to the Moorehead location, but since moving to SouthPark this is my new standard location. The staff is wonderful, the food is delish, and I always take home a bag of their coffee beans. Great location for working, or just hanging with friends.

review_questions.Parking options: Free street parking, Free parking garage

reviews_data.review_text: Wow, my new favorite deli! Love this hidden gem 💎.
Everything is always fresh and excellent. I adore food, and these were some of the nicest sandwiches and salads I've ever had. The service has always been prompt, amiable, and enthusiastic.
I love Rhino! I was counting down the days until this location opened and it does not disappoint! We go here every weekend for breakfast burritos, coffee and local beer.

I ordered online for pickup on a Sunday at 4:30pm. Drove to rhino and then got a text at 4:50 that my order was canceled.  Walked inside (at 4:50) and was told “No, we close at 5.”   We come here weekly and like the food but this is disappointing; will reconsider coming here in the future
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Lindsay
Sorry to hear this happened.
Which location did this occur?
Would like to offer a gift card to make up for your troubles.

reviews_data.review_text: Nice location and space. Good beverage selection. However, last night, kitchen was closed which was fine, but sandwich selection in fridge was poor. Got a Turkey and Havarti on Rye. It was mostly bread. One slice of Turkey, one thin slice of cheese and one leaf of lettuce. C’mon, do better for the price!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, Ana. I'm sorry we had to close the deli a little early last night for our regular kitchen hood cleaning. The sandwiches in our Grab and Go cooler are priced 3 to 4 dollars cheaper than the sandwiches on our menu because of how they're built. I hope you'll come back to try us again so you can judge us based on a normal experience.

reviews_data.review_text: Just ordered a hot roast beef with just pepper jack cheese and hlit came with everything on it. I was the only person in line.. people cannot listen just wasted 11 dollars on trash.
Everything is always delicious and fresh. Some of the best sandwiches and salads I ever had and I love food, service has always been fast and friendly and energetic

Every experience I have with Rhino Southpark, whether personally or professionally has been extraordinary! The entire team, from the store to the deli to the bar....pure excellence. Food is DELISH and the drinks are varied & plentiful. Its just a super place to hang out or order catering for the team. Grateful to be right across the street! Its my favorite place!
**Shoutout to Natasha who helped me place a deli pick-up order this morning for the team....she was amazing & helpful and pleasant to speak with. Top notch staff over there at Rhino SP!! ❤️
Love the Rhino for a casual after work Friday beet!  Deli is great too!
Very cool place to grab a snack and a beverage.
Great place for a quick lunch. Sandwiches tasted great and an awesome outdoor seating area.
Excellent food and wine.  Awesome customer service
This place has it all! Delightful service, wide selection for your post-walk snack and cocktail, and the most delicious peach popsicles! 🍑 We will definitely be regular customers!

The place just opened.
Nice pastrami sandwich.
Lot's of seating in and out.
It would be good if you had regular coffee also. Instead of only flavored ones..
Delightful
Nice new spot for beers and good sandwiches. Great patio
This place is pretty nice! There is a lot of selection and the people working there were very helpful.
Great breakfast and lunch sandwiches. Good selection of craft beers and wine.

Sandwich was delicious, picked up a few market items which were all equally delicious.
Everybody was extremely friendly and welcoming; It's a awesome addition to SouthPark and in a great spot.
I'll definitely be back.
Love the hot sicillian! But can you please change the bread back? The old bread was so good and the new bread is NOT
LOVE RHINO. Think the kitchen staff here is still figuring it out however!

Amazing addition to Southpark area, brilliant idea to put a Rhino market here, space is very flexible, super fast Wi-Fi, inviting outdoor patio with mature trees, nice bar with outlets. Utilitarian and relaxing at the same time.

So excited to have the Rhino Market in Southpark close to work and home, ifs very convenient, clean, well organized. I only gave 4 stars because hours and contact info for this location is not listed anywhere, and I went over the weekend to get breakfast and none of the breakfast sandwiches we ordered had eggs which was very strange as they all say they came with egg in the description. I'm sure that's just growing pains, but I had no where else to send that information. Will definitely be back :)
So glad they opened up in Southpark! Great food/drinks and the staff here are super friendly!

If you've had anything from Rhino's deli before you already know the food counter there is amazing - no change there.

More amazingly, this is the first shop I have ever walked out with an appreciation for the layout of everything - the deli ordering counter is right there as you walk in and the bar and groceries flank it on either side.  You can tell a lot of care was taken to make the most of the space.

Can't wait to go back!
Fresh new deli, had a great breakfast omelette here,
